<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n40195d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n40" href="#n40195d">N40 (VI.B.28B)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n40all.htm#n40195d"> 195(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> tears off &amp; / tramples diadem </blockquote> <dd class="well"><mm class="note">Note: On learning of Caesar&apos;s dalliance with his sister Cleoptara, and on being urged by him to restore her, as their father had willed, to the throne as his wife and co-regent, the boy Ptolemy wandered out into the street in a rage, tore off his diadem and trampled it underfoot. </mm> </dd></dl>
